content: This is one of, if not the, greatest film of all time. The fact that people do not like this movie for one reason or another, is ridiculous. Interstellar still to this day, is downright incredible in every aspect. I have it as #1 all time.

Almost as good as the Emoji Movie. The Emoji Movie is literally the greatest movie ever made and I am not exaggerating at all. From the first second, I was hooked because the colors are super bright and everything looks awesome, like your phone came to life in the best way possible. Emoji City is an amazing place and honestly seems like somewhere I would want to live. The animation is so good that it feels almost real, but better than real. Gene is such a relatable character because he doesn’t fit in, and that teaches an important lesson about being yourself even when people don’t get you. Hi-5 is really funny and a great friend, which proves friendship is important. And Jailbreak is AMAZING. She is smart, brave, confident, and let’s be honest, Jailbreak is hot. She has a cool jacket, cool hair, and a cool personality, which makes her iconic. The movie is funny, meaningful, and exciting the whole time. It deserves way more love and at least a million stars.
Best science fiction movie ever made
All time favorite film. Beautiful in every way.

10/10 movie Pretty high IQ to understand the plot but nothing too complex, the events and how the plot was concluded to save humanity was genius It sends a pretty cool message, and from my interpretation that message was: "your life is fully in your hands, there is no outside force that will tell you what to do, you have to figure it out and plan your future using your best odds"
